Regional Business Development Manager - Biologics

- Chemin des Aulx, 1228 Plan-les-Ouates, Switzerland
- Full-time

Company Description

The Regional Business Development Manager will sell our early phase Biological Characterisation testing services to 
clients within the Pharma and Biotech industries. SGS Life Sciences is a world leading GLP / cGMP contract analytical 
services group dedicated to providing high quality analysis of biopharmaceuticals. Studies involve molecules at all 
stages of product development. 

You Will: 

- Work in partnership with stakeholders at other SGS Biologics labs to develop service offerings and solutions;
- Actively prospect new clients and develop existing business accounts with a focus on providing value-added solutions 
and services;
- Monitor the Life Sciences market to identify trends and develop a tailored sales approach to take advantage of 
current or future issues facing clients;
- Produce accurate and detailed proposals for clients in accordance with SGS procedures, policies and pricing 
structure in a timely manner;
- Ensure that SGS has the necessary capability and resources to provide contracted services;
- Follow up on all proposals and conduct client presentations. Participate in conferences and attend trade shows;
- Ensure that master agreements are finalized and contracts are renewed or amended as necessary.

Qualifications

- Educated to Bachelors, Masters or PhD level in a Life Sciences related subject;
- Proven experience working in a Sales or Business Development position with a similar services portfolio;
- Background working as a Scientist in a lab environment or within the Pharmaceutical industry;
- Able to travel up to 60% of the time;
- Familiarity with US and EU regulatory processes beneficial;
- Fluent in English. Other languages are a benefit;

Additional Information

This position will be based at our lab in Plan-les-Ouates. We are also able to accommodate remote working in 
Switzerland or France. 

